<p>
  To create a media object, use an outer most &lt;div&gt; with a class of <code>media</code> assigned to it. Then add an image with a class of <code>media-object</code> optionally 
  wrapping it in a regular &lt;a&gt; element that has the alignment class of <code>pull-left</code> asigned, so that the image is both clickable and floated left.  The body of the media object 
  should be placed in an inner &lt;div&gt; element which has a class of <code>media-body</code> assigned to it.
</p>

